### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### FinanceHQ – Portfolio CRUD manual verification
###   Phase 2 manual checks:
###   2.2 All CRUD scenarios return expected status codes
###   2.3 Duplicate ticker POST returns 409 ProblemDetail
###   2.4 Cross-user isolation (asset created as user A is invisible to user B)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Prerequisites:
###   1. Server running on localhost:8080 with --spring.profiles.active=local
###   2. Select "dev" environment (top-right in IntelliJ HTTP Client)
###   3. Run auth-flow.http Steps 1–2 first to populate accessToken
###   4. Run requests IN ORDER

### ─── List — expect 200 with [] for a fresh user ───────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── Create (BTC) — expect 201; captures portfolioAssetId ─────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "BTC",
  "assetGroup": "Crypto",
  "shares": 0.5,
  "avgBuyPricePln": 150000.00,
  "avgBuyPriceAssetCurrency": 37500.00,
  "purchaseValuePln": 75000.00,
  "purchaseValueAssetCurrency": 18750.00,
  "purchaseSharePercent": 30.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("portfolioAssetId", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── List — expect 200, contains BTC ──────────────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── Update (PATCH shares + assetGroup) — expect 200 ──────────
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/{{portfolioAssetId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shares": 0.75,
  "assetGroup": "Digital Assets"
}


### ─── Delete — expect 204 ───────────────────────────────────────
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/{{portfolioAssetId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── List after delete — expect 200 with [] ───────────────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── Duplicate ticker (expect 409) ────────────────────────────
### First create AAPL, then try to create AAPL again
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "AAPL",
  "assetGroup": "US Stocks",
  "shares": 10.0,
  "avgBuyPricePln": 750.00,
  "avgBuyPriceAssetCurrency": 190.00,
  "purchaseValuePln": 7500.00,
  "purchaseValueAssetCurrency": 1900.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("aaplId", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── Second AAPL — expect 409 Conflict with ProblemDetail ─────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "AAPL",
  "assetGroup": "US Stocks",
  "shares": 5.0,
  "avgBuyPricePln": 800.00,
  "avgBuyPriceAssetCurrency": 200.00,
  "purchaseValuePln": 4000.00,
  "purchaseValueAssetCurrency": 1000.00
}


### ─── Cleanup AAPL ───────────────────────────────────────────────
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/{{aaplId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Phase 3 manual checks:
###   3.2 Refresh with real API keys populates prices for AAPL and BTC
###   3.3 Second refresh within 15 min returns "refreshed": false
###   3.4 PKN/XWAR asset receives a price from Twelve Data
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Prerequisites:
###   Set TWELVEDATA_API_KEY in application-local.properties

### ─── Create AAPL (security) ─────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "AAPL",
  "assetGroup": "US Stocks",
  "shares": 10.0,
  "avgBuyPricePln": 750.00,
  "avgBuyPriceAssetCurrency": 190.00,
  "purchaseValuePln": 7500.00,
  "purchaseValueAssetCurrency": 1900.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("aaplId2", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── Create BTC (crypto) ────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "BTC",
  "assetGroup": "Crypto",
  "shares": 0.5,
  "avgBuyPricePln": 150000.00,
  "avgBuyPriceAssetCurrency": 37500.00,
  "purchaseValuePln": 75000.00,
  "purchaseValueAssetCurrency": 18750.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("btcId", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── Create PKN/XWAR (GPW security) ────────────────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker": "PKN/XWAR",
  "assetGroup": "PL Stocks",
  "shares": 50.0,
  "avgBuyPricePln": 50.00,
  "avgBuyPriceAssetCurrency": 50.00,
  "purchaseValuePln": 2500.00,
  "purchaseValueAssetCurrency": 2500.00
}

> {%
  client.global.set("pknId", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── Refresh prices — expect "refreshed": true, prices populated ─
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/refresh-prices
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── Refresh again immediately — expect "refreshed": false ──────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/refresh-prices
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── Cleanup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/{{aaplId2}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/{{btcId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/{{pknId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Phase 4 manual checks:
###   4.2 Valid CSV import → correct asset count returned
###   4.3 Re-import same CSV → same count (UPSERT confirmed)
###   4.4 CSV with bad decimal → 422 with row number and column
###   4.5 File > 5 MB → 413 ProblemDetail (test manually with a large file)
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

### ─── Import CSV (valid, 3 assets) — expect 200 {"importedCount": 3} ─
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/import
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PortfolioBoundary

------PortfolioBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="portfolio.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

asset,shares,avg_buy_price_pln,avg_buy_price_asset_currency,purchase_value_pln,purchase_value_asset_currency,asset_group,purchase_share_percent
BTC,0.5,150000.00,37500.00,75000.00,18750.00,Crypto,30.00
ETH,2.0,8000.00,2000.00,16000.00,4000.00,Crypto,20.00
AAPL,10.0,750.00,190.00,7500.00,1900.00,US Stocks,50.00
------PortfolioBoundary--


### ─── Re-import same CSV — expect 200 {"importedCount": 3} (UPSERT, not 6) ─
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/import
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PortfolioBoundary

------PortfolioBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="portfolio.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

asset,shares,avg_buy_price_pln,avg_buy_price_asset_currency,purchase_value_pln,purchase_value_asset_currency,asset_group,purchase_share_percent
BTC,0.5,150000.00,37500.00,75000.00,18750.00,Crypto,30.00
ETH,2.0,8000.00,2000.00,16000.00,4000.00,Crypto,20.00
AAPL,10.0,750.00,190.00,7500.00,1900.00,US Stocks,50.00
------PortfolioBoundary--


### ─── Import CSV with bad decimal — expect 422 with rowErrors ───────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/import
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PortfolioBoundary

------PortfolioBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="bad.csv"
Content-Type: text/csv

asset,shares,avg_buy_price_pln,avg_buy_price_asset_currency,purchase_value_pln,purchase_value_asset_currency,asset_group
BTC,abc,150000.00,37500.00,75000.00,18750.00,Crypto
------PortfolioBoundary--


### ─── Import wrong content type (JSON) — expect 400 ────────────────
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/portfolio/import
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----PortfolioBoundary

------PortfolioBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="data.json"
Content-Type: application/json

{"ticker": "BTC"}
------PortfolioBoundary--
